}} [[Washington, D.C.|District of Columbia]]}}\n|{{dts|format=mdy|1991|1|2}}\n|{{dts|format=mdy|1995|1|2}}\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} |{{Party shortname|Democratic Party (United States)}}\n|First African American female mayor of a major city.<br>First female [[Mayor of the District of Columbia]].\n|{{nowrap|Lost renomination}}\n|-\n|[[File:Puerto Rican Governor Sila Calderon at the Pentagon, Feb 27, 2001.jpg|75px]]\n|{{nowrap|{{sortname|Sila|Calder\u00f3n|Sila Mar\u00eda Calder\u00f3n}}<br>{{small|(born 1942)}}\n|{{flagicon|Puerto Rico}} [[Puerto Rico]]\n|{{dts|format=mdy|2001|1|2}}\n|{{dts|format=mdy|2005|1|2}}\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} |{{nowrap|{{Party shortname|Popular Democratic Party (Puerto Rico)}}/}}<br>{{Party shortname|Democratic Party (United States)}}\n|First female [[Governor of Puerto Rico]].\n|Retired\n|- bgcolor=#E6E6AA\n|[[File:Muriel Bowser 2 cropped.jpg|75px]]\n|{{nowrap|{{sortname|Muriel|Bowser}}<br>{{small|(born 1972)}}\n|{{nowrap|{{flagicon|Washington, D.C.}} [[Washington, D.C.|District of Columbia]]}}\n|{{dts|format=mdy|2015|1|2}}\n|Incumbent \n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} |{{Party shortname|Democratic Party (United States)}}\n|\n|Serving\n|- bgcolor=#E6E6AA\n|[[File:Lou Leon Guerrero in 2018.jpeg|75px]]\n|{{sortname|Lou Leon|Guerrero}}<br>{{small|(born 1950)}}\n|{{nowrap|{{flagicon|Guam}} [[Guam]]}}\n|{{dts|format=mdy|2019|1|7}}\n|Incumbent \n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} |{{Party shortname|Democratic Party (United States)}}\n|First, and to date, only female [[List of Governors of Guam|Governor of Guam]].<br>First Pacific Islander American female Governor.\n|Serving\n|- bgcolor=#E6E6AA\n||[[File:Wanda Vasquez (cropped).jpg|75px]]\n|{{nowrap|{{sortname|Wanda|V\u00e1zquez Garced|Wanda V\u00e1zquez Garced}}<br>{{small|(born 1960)}}\n|{{flagicon|Puerto Rico}} [[Puerto Rico]]\n|{{dts|format=mdy|2019|8|7}}\n|Incumbent \n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |{{Party shortname|New Progressive Party (Puerto Rico)}}/<br>{{Party shortname|Republican 