{"title_page": "Rahul Deshpande", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=April 2018}}\n{{Multiple issues|\n{{notability|Music|date=June 2016}}\n{{tone|date=March 2015}}\n}}\n\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name            = Rahul Deshpande\n| image             =  Rahul Deshpande - Singing in Pune in March 2011.jpg\n| caption        = Rahul Deshpande - Singing in Pune in March 2011\n| native_name      = \u0930\u093e\u0939\u0941\u0932 \u0926\u0947\u0936\u092a\u093e\u0902\u0921\u0947\n| native_name_lang = mr\n| image_size        =\n| background      = solo_singer\n| birth_name      = \n| alias           =\n| birth_date      = {{Birth date and age|1979|10|10|df=y}}\n| birth_place     = [[Pune]], [[Maharashtra]], [[India]]\n| genre           = [[Hindustani classical music]]\n| occupation      = singer\n| years_active    = 1984 onwards\n| label           =\n| website         =\n}}\n\n'''Rahul Deshpande''' (born 10 October 1979) is an [[Indian classical music]] singer from [[Pune]], [[India]]. He is the grandson of [[Vasantrao Deshpande]] <ref>{{Cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/nagpur/Rahul-Deshpande-gives-a-Hatke-performance/articleshow/45838489.cms|title=Rahul Deshpande gives a \u2018Hatke\u2019 performance - Times of India|newspaper=The Times of India|access-date=2017-01-31}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.punemirror.in/entertainment/unwind/A-musical-extravaganza/articleshow/45825996.cms|title=A musical extravaganza - Pune Mirror -|newspaper=Pune Mirror|access-date=2017-01-31}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/thane/Three-day-arts-culture-carnival-at-Upvan-Lake/articleshow/46913608.cms|title=Three-day arts & culture carnival at Upvan Lake - Times of India|newspaper=The Times of India|access-date=2017-01-31}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Rahul Deshpande singing in Vasantotsav 2010.jpg|right|thumb|Rahul Deshpande singing in Vasantotsav 2010]]\n\n==Education and career==\nRahul developed his interest in vocal music by studying the music of [[Kumar Gandharva]]. Initially, he sought guidance of Pandit Gangadharbuva Pimpalkhare and Dr.Madhusudhan Patwardhan. He further learnt under the tutelage of Smt. Ushatai Chipalkatti and Pandit Mukul Shivputra. He also learned the [[tabla]] from Suresh Samant. His repertoire includes [[khyal]], [[thumri]], [[dadra]], [[natyageet]], [[bhajan]], [[ghazal]] and [[bhaavgeet]].\n\nRahul has judged Zee Marathi's popular reality TV show \"Sa Re Ga Ma Pa - Little Champs\" and Zee Yuva\u2019s \u201cSangeet Samrat parva2\u201d. His work in the re-opening of the musical play [[Katyar Kaljat Ghusali (play)|Katyar Kaljat Ghusali]] was appreciated.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/marathi/movies/news/Katyar-Kaljat-Ghusli-Subodh-Bhave-Mrunmayee-Deshpande-Rahul-Deshpande-Shankar-Mahadevan/articleshow/29151601.cms|title=Subodh and Mrunmayee in Katyar Kaljat Ghusli - Times of India|newspaper=The Times of India|access-date=2017-01-31}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.bollywoodlife.com/news-gossip/katyar-kaljat-ghusli-movie-review-subodh-bhave-sachin-pilgaonkar-and-shankar-mahadevan-give-an-unforgettable-diwali-treat-to-music-lovers/|title=Katyar Kaljat Ghusli movie review: Subodh Bhave, Sachin Pilgaonkar and Shankar Mahadevan give an unforgettable Diwali treat to music lovers!|last=Kulkarni|first=Preeti|language=en-US|access-date=2017-01-31}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.musicaloud.com/2015/11/04/katyar-kaljat-ghusli-music-review-marathi-soundtrack/|title=Katyar Kaljat Ghusli \u2013 Music Review (Marathi Soundtrack)|date=2015-11-04|website=Music Aloud|access-date=2017-01-31}}</ref> He was the playback singer for the songs of \"Khansaheb Aftab Hussain Bareliwale\", played by [[Sachin Pilgaonkar]] in the film. The role was played by Rahul himself in the play [[Katyar Kaljat Ghusali (play)|Katyar Kaljat Ghusali]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/lifestyle/report-revival-of-sangeet-natak-by-a-new-theatre-group-in-pune-1549091|title=Revival of sangeet-natak by a new theatre group in Pune {{!}} Latest News & Updates at Daily News & Analysis|date=2011-05-30|newspaper=dna|language=en-US|access-date=2017-01-31}}</ref>\n\nAlso, every year he arranges Vasantotsav in the memory of his grandfather [[Vasantrao Deshpande]].<ref name=\"Music across boundaries\">{{cite news|url=http://www.expressindia.com/latest-news/Music-across-boundaries/260099/|title=Music across boundaries|date=11 Jan 2008|publisher=Indian Express|language=English|accessdate=7 December 2010}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/pune/Classical-fusion-music-at-Vasantotsav/articleshow/45768085.cms|title=Classical, fusion music at Vasantotsav - Times of India|newspaper=The Times of India|access-date=2017-01-31}}</ref>\n\nA revised version of [[Krushnaji Prabhakar Khadilkar|Kakasaheb Khadilkar]]'s Sangeet Maanapmaan played in [[Maharashtra]] in 2011 and 2012, the centenary year of the play's first performance. It has been revised by Rahul Deshpande. \"Originally, the play has five parts with around 52 classical songs. Deshpande's version will have two parts and 22 classical songs.\"<ref name=\"bengrut\">{{cite news|url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/act-100/888011/|title=Act 100|last=Bengrut|first=Dheeraj|date=2011-12-15|work=indianexpress.com|publisher=The Indian Express Limited|location=Mumbai|via=|accessdate=15 February 2012}}</ref>\n\n=== Stage appearances ===\n{{Div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* ''[[Katyar Kaljat Ghusali (play)|Katyar Kaljat Ghusali]]''\n* ''Sangeet Sanshaykallol''\n* \u201cSangeet Manapman\u201d\n* \u201cSangeet Saubhadra\u201d\n{{div col end}}\n\n=== Filmography ===\n* ''[[Balgandharva (film)|Balgandharva]]''<ref name=\"Music\">{{cite web |url=http://www.balgandharvathefilm.com/press1.php |title=Recreating the magic of the Gandharva music |accessdate=16 December 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120502192230/http://www.balgandharvathefilm.com/press1.php |archivedate=2 May 2012 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> (Playback Singer)\n* ''[[Katyar Kaljat Ghusali (film)|Katyar Kaljat Ghusali]]'' (Playback Singer)\n* ''[[imdbtitle:7390064|Amaltash]]''<ref name=\"Movie\">{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt7390064|title=Rahul Deshpande stars as his late grandfather Vasantrao Deshpande in this biopic|last=|first=|date=|website=IMDB|url-status=live}}</ref> (Actor and Playback Singer) (Yet to be released)\n*''[[imdbtitle:11960634|Mee Vasantrao]]''<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt11960634/|title=Rahul Deshpande plays the role of his late grandfather Vasantrao Deshpande in this biopic|last=|first=|date=|website=IMDB|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> (Actor and Playback Singer) (Yet to be released)\n\n==Achievements and recognition==\n* ''Rasikagrani Dattopant Deshpande Award,'' presented to him at the ''[[Sawai Gandharva Music Festival]].''\n* Master Dinanath Mangeshkar Awards 2012 by Lata Mangeshkar.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://pages.rediff.com/photoalbum/preview/rediff-bollywood-photos/madhuri-dixit-nene-with-shiv-sena-leader-bal-thackeray-at-master-dinanath-mangeshkar-awards-2012/4352308/40457401/202510/18/lata-mangeshkar-presenting-award-to-singer-rahul-deshpande-at-master-dinanath-mangeshkar-awards-2012-in-mumbai|title=Lata Mangeshkar presenting award to singer Rahul Deshpande at Master Dinanath Mangeshkar Awards 2012 in Mumbai : rediff bollywood photos on Rediff Pages|website=pages.rediff.com|access-date=2017-01-31}}</ref> \n* \"Kothrud Bhushan\" award by the hands of Maharashtra's Chief Minister, Devendra Phadanvis. \n* ''[[Sudhir Phadke]] Award'' for his outstanding achievements at a young age.\n* Special Jury Award Best Singers in Zee Chitr Gaurav 2016.\n\n== Personal life==\nRahul is married to Neha Deshpande and they have a daughter.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/events/others/Raga-and-symphony/articleshow/3978787.cms|title=Raga and symphony|last=|first=|date=15 January 2009|work=|newspaper=The Times of India|access-date=2017-01-31|via=}}</ref>\n\n== References<ref name=\":0\" />==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Deshpande, Rahul}}\n[[Category:Hindustani singers]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Singers from Pune]]\n[[Category:Indian Hindus]]\n[[Category:Marathi-language singers]]\n[[Category:1979 births]]\n[[Category:Patiala gharana]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=April 2018}}\n{{Multiple issues|\n{{notability|Music|date=June 2016}}\n{{tone|date=March 2015}}\n}}\n\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name            = Rahul Deshpande\n| image             =  Rahul Deshpande - Singing in Pune in March 2011.jpg\n| caption        = Rahul Deshpande - Singing in Pune in March 2011\n| native_name      = \u0930\u093e\u0939\u0941\u0932 \u0926\u0947\u0936\u092a\u093e\u0902\u0921\u0947\n| native_name_lang = mr\n| image_size        =\n| background      = solo_singer\n| birth_name      = \n| alias           =\n| birth_date      = {{Birth date and age|1979|10|10|df=y}}\n| birth_place     = [[Pune]], [[Maharashtra]], [[India]]\n| genre           = [[Hindustani classical music]]\n| occupation      = singer\n| years_active    = 1984 onwards\n| label           =\n| website         =\n}}\n\n'''Rahul Deshpande''' (born 10 October 1979) is an [[Indian classical music]] singer from [[Pune]], [[India]]. He is the grandson of [[Vasantrao Deshpande]] <ref>{{Cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/nagpur/Rahul-Deshpande-gives-a-Hatke-performance/articleshow/45838489.cms|title=Rahul Deshpande gives a \u2018Hatke\u2019 performance - Times of India|newspaper=The Times of India|access-date=2017-01-31}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.punemirror.in/entertainment/unwind/A-musical-extravaganza/articleshow/45825996.cms|title=A musical extravaganza - Pune Mirror -|newspaper=Pune Mirror|access-date=2017-01-31}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/thane/Three-day-arts-culture-carnival-at-Upvan-Lake/articleshow/46913608.cms|title=Three-day arts & culture carnival at Upvan Lake - Times of India|newspaper=The Times of India|access-date=2017-01-31}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Rahul Deshpande singing in Vasantotsav 2010.jpg|right|thumb|Rahul Deshpande singing in Vasantotsav 2010]]\n\n==Education and career==\nRahul developed his interest in vocal music by studying the music of [[Kumar Gandharva]]. Initially, he sought guidance of Pandit Gangadharbuva Pimpalkhare and Dr.Madhusudhan Patwardhan. He further learnt under the tutelage of Smt. Ushatai Chipalkatti and Pandit Mukul Shivputra. He also learned the [[tabla]] from Suresh Samant. His repertoire includes [[khyal]], [[thumri]], [[dadra]], [[natyageet]], [[bhajan]], [[ghazal]] and [[bhaavgeet]].\n\nRahul has judged Zee Marathi's popular reality TV show \"Sa Re Ga Ma Pa - Little Champs\" and Zee Yuva\u2019s \u201cSangeet Samrat parva2\u201d. His work in the re-opening of the musical play [[Katyar Kaljat Ghusali]] was appreciated.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/marathi/movies/news/Katyar-Kaljat-Ghusli-Subodh-Bhave-Mrunmayee-Deshpande-Rahul-Deshpande-Shankar-Mahadevan/articleshow/29151601.cms|title=Subodh and Mrunmayee in Katyar Kaljat Ghusli - Times of India|newspaper=The Times of India|access-date=2017-01-31}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.bollywoodlife.com/news-gossip/katyar-kaljat-ghusli-movie-review-subodh-bhave-sachin-pilgaonkar-and-shankar-mahadevan-give-an-unforgettable-diwali-treat-to-music-lovers/|title=Katyar Kaljat Ghusli movie review: Subodh Bhave, Sachin Pilgaonkar and Shankar Mahadevan give an unforgettable Diwali treat to music lovers!|last=Kulkarni|first=Preeti|language=en-US|access-date=2017-01-31}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.musicaloud.com/2015/11/04/katyar-kaljat-ghusli-music-review-marathi-soundtrack/|title=Katyar Kaljat Ghusli \u2013 Music Review (Marathi Soundtrack)|date=2015-11-04|website=Music Aloud|access-date=2017-01-31}}</ref> He was the playback singer for the songs of \"Khansaheb Aftab Hussain Bareliwale\", played by [[Sachin Pilgaonkar]] in the film. The role was played by Rahul himself in the play [[Katyar Kaljat Ghusali (play)|Katyar Kaljat Ghusali]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/lifestyle/report-revival-of-sangeet-natak-by-a-new-theatre-group-in-pune-1549091|title=Revival of sangeet-natak by a new theatre group in Pune {{!}} Latest News & Updates at Daily News & Analysis|date=2011-05-30|newspaper=dna|language=en-US|access-date=2017-01-31}}</ref>\n\nAlso, every year he arranges Vasantotsav in the memory of his grandfather [[Vasantrao Deshpande]].<ref name=\"Music across boundaries\">{{cite news|url=http://www.expressindia.com/latest-news/Music-across-boundaries/260099/|title=Music across boundaries|date=11 Jan 2008|publisher=Indian Express|language=English|accessdate=7 December 2010}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/pune/Classical-fusion-music-at-Vasantotsav/articleshow/45768085.cms|title=Classical, fusion music at Vasantotsav - Times of India|newspaper=The Times of India|access-date=2017-01-31}}</ref>\n\nA revised version of [[Krushnaji Prabhakar Khadilkar|Kakasaheb Khadilkar]]'s Sangeet Maanapmaan played in [[Maharashtra]] in 2011 and 2012, the centenary year of the play's first performance. It has been revised by Rahul Deshpande. \"Originally, the play has five parts with around 52 classical songs. Deshpande's version will have two parts and 22 classical songs.\"<ref name=\"bengrut\">{{cite news|url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/act-100/888011/|title=Act 100|last=Bengrut|first=Dheeraj|date=2011-12-15|work=indianexpress.com|publisher=The Indian Express Limited|location=Mumbai|via=|accessdate=15 February 2012}}</ref>\n\n=== Stage appearances ===\n{{Div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* ''[[Katyar Kaljat Ghusali (play)|Katyar Kaljat Ghusali]]''\n* ''Sangeet Sanshaykallol''\n* \u201cSangeet Manapman\u201d\n* \u201cSangeet Saubhadra\u201d\n{{div col end}}\n\n=== Filmography ===\n* ''[[Balgandharva (film)|Balgandharva]]''<ref name=\"Music\">{{cite web |url=http://www.balgandharvathefilm.com/press1.php |title=Recreating the magic of the Gandharva music |accessdate=16 December 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120502192230/http://www.balgandharvathefilm.com/press1.php |archivedate=2 May 2012 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> (Playback Singer)\n* ''[[Katyar Kaljat Ghusali (film)|Katyar Kaljat Ghusali]]'' (Playback Singer)\n* ''[[imdbtitle:7390064|Amaltash]]''<ref name=\"Movie\">{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt7390064|title=Rahul Deshpande stars as his late grandfather Vasantrao Deshpande in this biopic|last=|first=|date=|website=IMDB|url-status=live}}</ref> (Actor and Playback Singer) (Yet to be released)\n*''[[imdbtitle:11960634|Mee Vasantrao]]''<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt11960634/|title=Rahul Deshpande plays the role of his late grandfather Vasantrao Deshpande in this biopic|last=|first=|date=|website=IMDB|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> (Actor and Playback Singer) (Yet to be released)\n\n==Achievements and recognition==\n* ''Rasikagrani Dattopant Deshpande Award,'' presented to him at the ''[[Sawai Gandharva Music Festival]].''\n* Master Dinanath Mangeshkar Awards 2012 by Lata Mangeshkar.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://pages.rediff.com/photoalbum/preview/rediff-bollywood-photos/madhuri-dixit-nene-with-shiv-sena-leader-bal-thackeray-at-master-dinanath-mangeshkar-awards-2012/4352308/40457401/202510/18/lata-mangeshkar-presenting-award-to-singer-rahul-deshpande-at-master-dinanath-mangeshkar-awards-2012-in-mumbai|title=Lata Mangeshkar presenting award to singer Rahul Deshpande at Master Dinanath Mangeshkar Awards 2012 in Mumbai : rediff bollywood photos on Rediff Pages|website=pages.rediff.com|access-date=2017-01-31}}</ref> \n* \"Kothrud Bhushan\" award by the hands of Maharashtra's Chief Minister, Devendra Phadanvis. \n* ''[[Sudhir Phadke]] Award'' for his outstanding achievements at a young age.\n* Special Jury Award Best Singers in Zee Chitr Gaurav 2016.\n\n== Personal life==\nRahul is married to Neha Deshpande and they have a daughter.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/events/others/Raga-and-symphony/articleshow/3978787.cms|title=Raga and symphony|last=|first=|date=15 January 2009|work=|newspaper=The Times of India|access-date=2017-01-31|via=}}</ref>\n\n== References<ref name=\":0\" />==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Deshpande, Rahul}}\n[[Category:Hindustani singers]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Singers from Pune]]\n[[Category:Indian Hindus]]\n[[Category:Marathi-language singers]]\n[[Category:1979 births]]\n[[Category:Patiala gharana]]\n", "name_user": "Rodw", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguating links toKatyar Kaljat Ghusali(link changed toKatyar Kaljat Ghusali (play)) usingDisamAssist.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rahul_Deshpande"}
